snippet.textDisplay: You somehow read my mind. I rented one a few yrs  ago, it was a manual trans. Honeslty i dont mind  selling my current project car (960 volvo, yeah who does drive a rwd box with wheels? Me lol) and get a Mazda MX5. Congratulations!! And yeah its black but you know, it does have its dark toned lines that makes the car looks a bit misterious, you dont really know till you see it up close, yeah its cool i like it, and if you wrapped in yellow even better ✌.

snippet.textDisplay: Great video. I have an NA that I have been working on for years and I love it. I used to work at Long Road Racing and I helped build roughly 65 of the ND MX-5 cup cars in 2018 and 2019. I loved working on those cars all the time and I would always find little fascinating tidbits of where they tried to lose weight and such. Very cool car with a lot of very cool details. Also, I have rebuilt/upgraded over 200 of those transmissions with racing gears and have seen just about every failure. Also I've installed a few Edelbrock superchargers so if you have any questions, I got you mate!
snippet.textOriginal: Great video. I have an NA that I have been working on for years and I love it. I used to work at Long Road Racing and I helped build roughly 65 of the ND MX-5 cup cars in 2018 and 2019. I loved working on those cars all the time and I would always find little fascinating tidbits of where they tried to lose weight and such. Very cool car with a lot of very cool details. Also, I have rebuilt/upgraded over 200 of those transmissions with racing gears and have seen just about every failure. Also I've installed a few Edelbrock superchargers so if you have any questions, I got you mate!

snippet.textDisplay: I outdragged an NSX in my Toyota Tercel. It wasn’t because of the Tercel’s brute power but the NSX owner being a dick. As we cane to a red traffic light together, I was double clutching my way down to first while the guy beside me stayed in top gear. The light turned green before we had to stop but I was in first and immediately hit it. The NSX driver, too, floored it but he had no RPM or power. I stayed ahead until we arrived at the speed limit when his car finally got into its power band and hit warp speed and disappeared into the distance.

snippet.textDisplay:
ND Miata 1st: 5.087 x 2.866 = 14.579342 : 1
AP1 S2000 1st: 3.133 x 1.16 x 4.10 = 14.900547 : 1

The S2000 has more aggressive gearing.
The AP1 has a 1.16 secondary reduction, and the AP2 has a 1.208333 secondary reduction, making the AP2 even more aggressive.
